Sentencas: Single- and double-doped YBa(Fe,Co,Cu)(2)O5+delta layered perovskites are prepared by solid state reaction method and their structural characteristics, thermal expansion coefficient, oxygen nonstoichiometry, electrical conductivity, and electrochemical performance are comparatively studied.
Titulo: Structural and electrochemical characterization of YBa(Fe,Co,Cu)2O5+δ layered perovskites as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The substitution of Co by Fe or/and Cu significantly improves thermal expansion properties as compared to undoped YBaCo2O5+delta.
Titulo: Structural and electrochemical characterization of YBa(Fe,Co,Cu)2O5+δ layered perovskites as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical tests demonstrate the promising performance of synthesized materials as cathode materials at intermediate temperatures.
Titulo: Structural and electrochemical characterization of YBa(Fe,Co,Cu)2O5+δ layered perovskites as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Single doped YBaCuCoO5+delta cathodes reveal the lowest polarization resistance equal to 0.24 and 0.78 Omega cm(2) at P(O-2) P-1 = 0.2 at temperature of 800 and 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Structural and electrochemical characterization of YBa(Fe,Co,Cu)2O5+δ layered perovskites as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells
